#include<iostream>
#include<cmath>
#include<string>
using namespace std;
bool isleap(int y)
{
	if(y%400==0 || (y%100!=0 && y%4==0))
		return true;
	return false;
}
int main()
{
	int t,totday,day,month,year,i,k;
	string date;
	bool b;
	cin>>t;
	int days[13]={0,31,28,31,30,31,30,31,31,30,31,30,31};
	for(k=1;k<=t;k++)
	{
		cin>>date;
		day=(date[0]-'0')*10+(date[1]-'0');
		year=(date[7]-'0')*1000+(date[8]-'0')*100+(date[9]-'0')*10+(date[10]-'0');
		b=isleap(year);
		if(b)
			days[2]=29;
		else
			days[2]=28;
		if(date[3]=='J'&&date[5]=='N'&&date[4]=='A')
			month=1;
		if(date[3]=='F')
			month=2;
		if(date[3]=='M'&&date[5]=='R')
			month=3;
		if(date[3]=='A'&&date[4]=='P')
			month=4;
		if(date[3]=='M'&&date[5]=='Y')
			month=5;
		if(date[3]=='J'&&date[5]=='N'&&date[4]=='U')
			month=6;
		if(date[3]=='J'&&date[5]=='L'&&date[4]=='U')
			month=7;
		if(date[3]=='A'&&date[4]=='U')
			month=8;
		if(date[3]=='S')
			month=9;
		if(date[3]=='O')
			month=10;
		if(date[3]=='N')
			month=11;
		if(date[3]=='D')
			month=12;
		totday=0;
		for(i=1;i<month;i++)
			totday+=days[i];
		totday+=day;
		//cout<<day<<" "<<month<<" "<<year<<" "<<totday<<endl;
		if(totday<=300)
		{
			cout<<"Case "<<k<<": "<<totday<<" Hundreds"<<endl;
		}
		else if(totday<=360)
		{
			cout<<"Case "<<k<<": "<<(totday-300)<<" Tens"<<endl;
		}
		else
		{
			cout<<"Case "<<k<<": "<<(totday-360)<<" Ones"<<endl;
		}
	}
	return 0;
}
